    <svcsection id="s02003" division="truck" formnum="CTS-5148" date="04/08/1996">
        <title>FRONT AXLE LOCKING HUBS</title>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <truckmodelgroup/>

                <truckmodel>4000</truckmodel>
                <ucodegroup/>

                <ucode>02915</ucode>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <title>GENERAL</title>
                <para>Locking hubs provide a means of controlling engagement of the front wheels with the driving axle.
                    The purpose of this is to reduce driveline wear and increase fuel mileage. When the locking hubs are
                    engaged or in the "LOCK" position, full power is transmitted to both wheels. When the locking hubs
                    are disengaged or in the "FREE" position, the front wheels will turn independently of the front axle
                    shafts.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
    </svcsection>
